events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Kemba Walker couldn't have envisioned this Christmas.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walker's triple-double leads Knicks over Hawks, 101-87

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo said he tried to set low expectations for himself when he returned to action Saturday for the first time since entering the NBA’s health and safety protocols on Dec. 12.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks rally late in Antetokounmpo's return for 117-113 win

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — The Golden State Warriors kept it close despite being short-handed, setting the stage for a player to take over down the stretch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Warriors beat Suns 116-107 to regain top spot in NBA

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell dribbled out the clock in the backcourt, dodging Dallas' last-ditch efforts to foul before letting out a triumphant yell and throwing the ball high in the air.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell, Jazz rally past short-handed Mavs 120-116
